OL,6,FThe 'Fatal Four' are the four main
OL,7,Fcauses of deaths on our roads. They
OL,8,Fare impairment from drink or drugs,
OL,9,Fdistraction including mobile phones,
OL,10,Fspeeding and not wearing a seatbelt.
OL,11,FRoads policing officers will be out in
OL,12,Fforce with increased patrols across
OL,13,FHampshire and Isle of Wight for the
OL,14,Fwhole month of April, as part of a
OL,15,Fnational campaign to target motorists
OL,16,Fwho are committing these offences.
OL,17,FDetective Constable Mark Furse, who
OL,18,Fwas the Family Liaison Officer for
OL,19,FAlex's relatives, said: "This was a
OL,20,Fterrible incident where three people
OL,21,Flost their lives because of one man's
OL,22,Fselfish actions.J"Using your mobile
OL,23,Fphone is a huge distraction when
OL,24,Fdriving but sadly we still see people
OL,25,Fdoing this every day.J"Nothing is so
OL,26,Fimportant that it justifies using your
