OL,6,FIan Britton, Alex's father, said:
OL,7,F"She's always in our thoughts, we have
OL,8,Ftimes when we'll sit here and think
OL,9,Fabout some of the good times we had,
OL,10,Fand then also think about the day.
OL,11,F"I've now had to get counselling to
OL,12,Fdeal with the grief, no one should
OL,13,Fever have to bury their children
OL,14,Fbefore them."JAvril Swain, Alex's
OL,15,Fmother, said: "When I actually found
OL,16,Fout that he had been on his phone...
OL,17,Funimaginable, actually, that somebody
OL,18,Fin charge of that huge lorry would
OL,19,Ftake his eyes off the road to look at
OL,20,Fhis phone.J"Since the day of this
OL,21,Fincident, our lives have changed
OL,22,Fforever. There's no turning back from
OL,23,Fit. It was catastrophic.J"If anybody
OL,24,Fis thinking about even peeking at
OL,25,Ftheir phone whilst driving, just
OL,26,Fdon't. Whatever it is, it can wait
